Companion touch-tooltip: let a single touch TAP show a native menu tooltip (item stats, map-marker
name, etc.) when "Touch input" is on. ToolTips::update early-returns in GUI mode when the cursor
isn't visible; touch hides the game cursor, so tooltips never showed. Hold the gate open while touch
drives the menus (tooltip delay defaults to 0, so it appears at the tap point immediately).

Refined: the touch term now also requires TOUCH to be the ACTIVE input (!joystickLastUsed()) — a
touch tap clears joystickLastUsed (MouseManager), any controller press sets it. Without this, while
navigating a controller menu with touch merely ENABLED (not used), the term held the tooltip open
regardless of getControllerTooltipVisible, so R3 only FROZE the tooltip on the current item instead
of hiding it. Gating on the active input makes R3 hide/show cleanly under the controller (matching
touch-off) while a real tap still shows its tooltip. Needs <../mwbase/inputmanager.hpp>.
